{
  "doc_id": "41170",
  "text": "Here we show that a mutation in Arcn1 is responsible for the phenotypes in an ENU-induced mouse mutant, nur17, which was identified by screening for mice with both diluted coat color and ataxia. We identified a missense mutation in Arcn1 in nur17 mice and confirmed that it is responsible for coat color dilution and PC degeneration by transgenic rescue. ARCN1, also known as d-COP, is a sub-unit of the coat protein I (COPI) complex, which comprises one of the protein coats that mediate vesicle budding from the membrane (reviewed in [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] ). Thus, nur17 mice provide a unique model to study the intracellular trafficking and its association with neuronal function and pigmentation in mammals.",
